98
00:07:27.810 --> 00:07:30.760
So another important reason to practice your English with non-native speakers is

99
00:07:30.760 --> 00:07:34.120
Because your chances of having to communicate with them are so high.

100
00:07:35.520 --> 00:07:40.020
Even in an English-speaking country, there are typically hundreds of thousands, or in the case of the U.S.,

101
00:07:40.300 --> 00:07:43.120
Millions of people who speak English as a second language.

102
00:07:43.610 --> 00:07:47.810
And you need to be able to understand them just as much as you need to understand a native speaker. Right?

